I am pleased to see #USMCA  pass the House with strong bipartisan support.
 Idaho farmers and ranchers need fair, free trade to compete and this deal provides a level playing field. https://simpson.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=398832 …
After careful consideration of the evidence I voted no on #impeachment and here’s why https://simpson.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=398830 …

Our troops work tirelessly each and every day to promote global security and protect the American way of life, and I am proud to support a bill that supports them. #NDAA https://simpson.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=398829 …

Idaho farmers and ranchers feed the world and their greatest needs are a legal workforce and free trade, and this week we made tremendous progress on both issues. https://simpson.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=398828 …

We have real work to do and this madness should come to an end.

See my full statement regarding impeachment below: https://simpson.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=398820 …

Thank you @britter for your support of the Farm Workforce Modernization Act. 
This bill, much like #USMCA, matters to Idaho farmers & it's important that we deliver. https://twitter.com/ThisSpudsForYou/status/1204451685046898693 …

While most of the world was watching the theatrical impeachment hearing in the House, Republicans were at work. On Monday, I joined 159 Republicans sending Speaker Nancy Pelosi a letter urging her to immediately consider and pass the U.S.-Mexico-Canada Agreement (#USMCA).
This is phenomenal, well done to the employees of the @INL. https://twitter.com/Dr_Mark_Peters/status/1202686390934233088 …

Baseball is America’s pastime and that pastime should not be exclusive to a select number of cities. 
I am proud to join my colleagues in starting this task force to ensure baseball stays vibrant in communities like Idaho Falls and Boise ⚾️ https://twitter.com/EastIDNews/status/1202336521547706369 …
Thanks to @GovernorLittle and the Idaho legislature, Idahoans will enjoy the benefits of #RedTapeReduction https://twitter.com/GovernorLittle/status/1202308617594011648 …
I want to congratulate Dan Brouillette on his confirmation as the new Secreterary of @ENERGY. This is important work for the state of Idaho and our nation and you have my full support.
